# Siege project discipline

This project uses skills from [claude-configs-public](https://github.com/siege-analytics/claude-configs-public). Personal skills live in `~/.cursor/skills/`; project-specific skills may live in `.cursor/skills/`.

## Before implementation

For non-trivial work, follow the `think` skill: design note with ticket context, blast radius, alternatives, and explicit approval before code changes.

## Git and tickets

- Branch naming: `type/descriptive-string` (see `branch` skill)
- Commits reference tickets (see `commit` skill)
- PRs link tickets bidirectionally (see `create-pr` skill)
- Claim tickets with `pre-work-check` before starting work

## Always-on rules

Policy is in `~/.cursor/siege-rules-bundle.md` (personal install). Key cohorts: definition-of-done, writing-prose, writing-code, data-trust, principles.

## Cursor limitation

Hooks and PreToolUse gates from Claude Code are not available in Cursor. Compliance is via skill adherence and explicit self-review — not mechanical blocking.
